                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="101270" author="rwinch" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 14:55:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this should be explicitly added sine the nekohtml dependency is not necessary all of the time. It is only used with certain setups (i.e. attribute exchange).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="101362" author="doom777" created="Thu, 3 Apr 2014 02:41:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well even some sample apps provided by spring fail because of this. Attribute exchange is a major function of spring-security-openid, and should be supported out of the box. Generally declaring a dependency on spring-security-openid should be sufficient for all but exotic setups.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="101373" author="rwinch" created="Thu, 3 Apr 2014 06:19:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fair enough...this is now scheduled for the next patch release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="101374" author="rwinch" created="Thu, 3 Apr 2014 06:20:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;PS Thanks for your report and persistence in making Spring Security better &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="101376" author="doom777" created="Thu, 3 Apr 2014 06:47:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are welcome. Remember to change the status of the issue. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, eventually openid will have to be deprecated entirely, as it seems that the industry is moving to OpenID-Connect which is based on OAuth2 and not on openid at all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OID-Connect will have to be integrated into Spring also, but it&apos;s probably wise to wait until it gets at least some market penetration. This will also probably be needed to integrated into spring-security-oauth subproject or spring-social&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="101377" author="rwinch" created="Thu, 3 Apr 2014 07:06:33 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt; Remember to change the status of the issue&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks...done&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
